data-triple-N3.o: "The Lebanese Phalanges Party, better known in English as the Phalange, is a traditional right-wing political-paramilitary ultranationalist organization. Although it is officially secular, it is mainly supported by Maronite Christians. The party played a major role in the Lebanese Civil War (197590). In decline in the late 1980s and 1990s, the party slowly re-emerged since the early 2000s. It is now part of the March 14 Alliance."@en
